milestones.description: Andy Roberts and Joel Garner's 71-run partnership is the highest for the 10th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 64 between Deryck Murray and Andy Roberts
Syed Kirmani has broken the record for most dismissals in an innings (3) in ODIs for IND, going past Pochiah Krishnamurthy's 2
Andy Roberts and Joel Garner's 71-run partnership is WI's highest for the 10th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 64 between Deryck Murray and Andy Roberts
Yashpal Sharma and Roger Binny's 73-run partnership is IND's highest for the 6th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 68 between Kapil Dev and Yashpal Sharma

stories.title: The sightseers who won a world title
stories.subTitle: My First World Cup
stories.seoTitle: 1983 World Cup - Sandeep Patil on his first World Cup
stories.summary: India's 1983 World Cup squad was more keen to take in the sights of London than worry about facing Marshall and Co

image.caption: Sandeep Patil contributed to the campaign with an unbeaten 32-ball 51 in the semi-final against England
image.longCaption: Sandeep Patil of India batting during the World Cup semi-final against England at Old Trafford, 1983

stories.title: India stun the world
stories.subTitle: The 1983 World Cup in England
stories.summary: How the rank outsiders who had won only one match in their previous two World Cups dethroned the mightiest outfit of the day on the biggest stage
